Iona Costello, 51, and daughter Emily were visiting Manhattan when they went missing on March 30 near their home in Greenport, New York .
They were recognized by the front desk manager of the hotel they were staying at on Sunday, it was reported .
Police said they are now considering the case to be closed .
It comes after more details emerged of the colorful background of Mrs Costello's late husband George, who died from a heart attack in 2012 .